The Otaqo template was analysed as an inspiration source for layout and visual design patterns used for simialr themed websites.

Design Features:
- Strong visual hierarchy
- Clear section separation makes it easy for users to understand the structure of the page
- High quality imagery
- Images are aligned with content sections
- Consistent typography
- Font sizes and spacing are consistent across headings and body text, improving readability
- Clear section labelling
- Sections such as facilities, services, and membership are clearly labelled, helping users navigate content easily
- The layout adapts well to different screen sizes, ensuring a better mobile experience.

The research identified several important UX improvements to apply in the redesigned website:
- Improve navigation clarity and contrast
- Use consistent typography and left-aligned text
- Structure content into clear sections with headings
- Ensure mobile responsiveness
- Improve visual hierarchy and spacing
- Integrate images more consistently within the layout
- Clearly label important sections such as Find Us / Location

These insights informed the design decisions for the redesigned club website.
